creator: Joseph W. Zaehnsdorf
description:
LibriVox recording of The Art of Bookbinding by Joseph W. Zaehnsdorf.
Read in English by Amelia Chesley; Maria Kasper; Melvin Lee; Availle
This handbook explains the art of bookbinding and simultaneously reminds us what a complex technology is to make books! Zaehnsdorf, bookbinder and son of a bookbinder, made this second edition of his book to enlighten amateurs and tradesmen alike. The whole process of binding a book and the required equipment are carefully explained to the reader. Summary by kathrinee
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
